sslTips:
The automatic SSL certificate function requires adding a certificate named PhpWebStudy-Root-CA to the certificate store and setting it to always trust

Normally, this function will be automatically completed.

If this function is abnormal. You can also copy and execute commands on the terminal.

You can also find the certificate file in the opened folder. And manually add the certificate to the Trusted Root Certification Authorities folder of the certificate store

dnsInfo:
Turn on a DNS server. Resolve the domain name set in the /etc/hosts file to the local ip. Mainly used for other computers or phones on the LAN to access the local site. 
This feature requires node, so if you don't have it installed, please install it first.
How to use.
1. Start the DNS server.
2. On other computers or phones, set the DNS of the network, enter the DNS IP displayed in the current interface. It is best to keep only this one DNS setting, and then restore the original setting after it is no longer in use.
3. Use this command for testing: dig {ip} domain
4. On other computers or phones, use the domain name of the local site to access.
